snippet.title: Żabson, Pezet, god.wifi, Asster - GUARDIAN ANGEL ULTRA MAX (Def Jam World Tour)
snippet.description:
„GUARDIAN ANGEL ULTRA MAX” available at: https://DefJamWorldTour.lnk.to/GUARDIANANGELULTRAMAX

Def Jam World Tour is a series of trips organised by the label to locations all around the world. For each stop, Def Jam invites a few artists from Poland to work with local producers, giving them the opportunity to create unexpected collaborations. After visiting Bucharest, Johannesburg, Paris, Berlin, and London, the project has now reached Los Angeles – the global epicentre of the music industry. The result of an intense three-day creative session is nine brand-new tracks. Follow the journey on social media @defjampl.

Bruno Mars is a 16x GRAMMY®-winning global superstar, singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, producer, and one of the most-streamed artists in the world. Known for his showmanship and chart-toppers, Bruno has set a number of records throughout his career, including becoming the first artist ever to hit 150 million monthly listeners on Spotify, appearing on two of the fastest songs to reach one billion streams (for “Die with a Smile” with Lady Gaga and “APT.” with ROSÉ, and achieving the highest-certified song in RIAA history with 2010’s “Just the Way You Are”). Since launching a string of hits beginning in 2009, Bruno has sold over 150 million records worldwide, making him one of the best-selling artists of all time. Beyond his work as a soloist, Bruno is a member of the duo Silk Sonic with Anderson .Paak. In addition to his 35 Billboard Hot 100 hits, including nine number one singles, Bruno is the recipient of 16 GRAMMY® Awards (including “Album of the Year” for 24K Magic), 14 American Music Awards, and seven MTV Video Music Awards. His 24K Magic World Tour was among the highest-grossing tours in history, and within the top ten highest-grossing of the 2010s.

snippet.title: Stasiek Kukulski - This too shall pass (Eurovision2026 POLAND - preselekcje)
snippet.description:
Follow Stasiek Kukulski:

INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/stasiek.kukulski_music?igsh=MW5qMDBtdGtvbmd6dg%3D%3D&utm_source=qr
FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/share/1C5omfPbt3/?mibextid=wwXIfr

„This too shall pass” to motto, które ma być pocieszeniem za każdym razem, gdy życie rzuca na drodze przeszkodę. Bez względu na to, jak ciężka, zagmatwana czy bolesna wydaje się ta chwila, wszystko przemija. 
Jeśli więc dziś mierzysz się z czymś trudnym, trzymaj się. Oddychaj. Zaufaj. Burza nie będzie trwała wiecznie, a Ty wyjdziesz z niej silniejszy.


“This too shall pass” is a phrase meant to bring comfort every time life places an obstacle in your path. No matter how difficult, complicated, or painful the moment may seem, everything passes.
So if today you are facing something hard, hold on. Breathe. Trust. The storm will not last forever, and you will come out of it stronger.

#eurovision2026 #thistooshallpass #stasiekkukulski

Lyrics

oh, jay, sing into my ear
and raise me above my fear
through the night, from my weary heart
with dawn, from my bare soul, dearest guard

i’m near the edge of surrender
this too shall pass
the only thing to remember
this too shall pass
for it couldn’t last

oh, jay, let thy wings take flight
may I bathe into the sky?
In the dark, in the abyss, shadows dwell.

whether the storm will fade or stay
Whether the night whether the day

i’m near the edge of surrender
this too shall pass
the only thing to remember
this too shall pass
for it couldn’t last

Tłumaczenie

śpiewaj sójko, śpiewaj mi
strach mój weź, odwagą tchnij
pilnuj w noc, gdy znużone serce me
zanim świt, osłoń duszę nagą w gęstej mgle

o krawędź, lecz się nie poddam
przeminie i to
i rozpacz mą, gniew mój oddam
przeminie i to
z mą ostatnią łzą

sójko rozłóż skrzydła swe
bym do nieba uniósł się
w dole cień, otchłań, ciemność wciąż przyzywa mnie

czy burza trwa czy gaśnie już
czy noc czy dzień czy wiatr czy kurz

o krawędź, lecz się nie poddam
przeminie i to
i rozpacz mą, gniew mój oddam
przeminie i to
z mą ostatnią łzą
